Definition: the opportunity cost of the funds employed as the result of an investment decision
Example: the rate of return that a business could earn if it chose another investment with equivalent risk
Synonyms: capital_cost, opportunity_cost, the, opportunity, cost, of, funds, employed, as, result, an, investment, decision, rate, return, that, a, business, could, earn, if, it, chose, another, with, equivalent, risk
Category: noun.possession
